# TypeScript & Code Quality Validation Infrastructure (Handover Report)

This report details the specialized scripts and automated gates implemented (primarily on Jan 31, 2026) to manage TypeScript integrity and WordPress Block Grammar compliance in the PressPilot-OS project.

---

## 1. Automated Gatekeeper (Husky)
We have implemented a strict pre-commit hook using **Husky** to ensure no code reaches the repository with TypeScript errors.

- **Hook**: [.husky/pre-commit](file:///Users/soluwrx/Downloads/PressPilot-OS/PressPilot-OS/.husky/pre-commit)
- **Command**: `npx tsc --noEmit --skipLibCheck`
- **Purpose**: This prevents "TypeScript problems" at the source by blocking commits if the compiler finds any type mismatches or syntax errors.

---

## 2. Specialized Validators (The "Hard Gates")
Beyond standard TS checking, we use custom scripts to validate the **logic and output** of the theme generator.

### A. WordPress FSE Validator ([scripts/validateGenerator.ts](file:///Users/soluwrx/Downloads/PressPilot-OS/PressPilot-OS/scripts/validateGenerator.ts))
This is the most critical logic validator. It enforces "Hard Gates" on the generated theme output or templates.
- **Run with**: `npx tsx scripts/validateGenerator.ts <path-to-theme>`
- **Checks**:
  - **Structural Gate**: Uses a stack-based parser to ensure every `<!-- wp:block -->` has a matching `<!-- /wp:block -->`.
  - **JSON Gate**: Validates that all block attributes are valid, non-corrupted JSON.
  - **Hard Rules Gate**: Blocks forbidden attributes (like `"ref"`) and ensures all `var(--wp--preset)` variables exist in the theme's `theme.json`.
  - **Discipline Gate**: Enforces a maximum nesting depth (8 levels) to prevent WordPress editor instability.

### B. Library Validator ([scripts/validate-proven-cores.ts](file:///Users/soluwrx/Downloads/PressPilot-OS/PressPilot-OS/scripts/validate-proven-cores.ts))
Ensures the "Golden Skeletons" in `proven-cores/` are error-free.
- **Purpose**: Scans all PHP/HTML files in the library for malformed block comments before they are used as blueprints for theme generation.

### C. Token Security ([src/generator/validators/TokenValidator.ts](file:///Users/soluwrx/Downloads/PressPilot-OS/PressPilot-OS/src/generator/validators/TokenValidator.ts))
A runtime module integrated into the generation engine.
- **Purpose**: Sanitizes and validates data tokens passed from the Studio to the Generator, preventing corrupted strings or illegal characters from breaking the FSE block grammar.

---

## 3. Deployment & Build Integration
The [package.json](file:///Users/soluwrx/Downloads/PressPilot-OS/PressPilot-OS/package.json) includes scripts that chain these validations:

- **`npm run lint`**: Runs Next.js standard linting.
- **`npm run theme:build`**: Automatically runs [validateGenerator.ts](file:///Users/soluwrx/Downloads/PressPilot-OS/PressPilot-OS/scripts/validateGenerator.ts) against a "golden-spec" before proceeding with the build.
- **`npm run test:themes`**: Generates and validates a battery of test themes.

---

## 4. End-to-End Regression Scripts
To "fix" problems proactively, we use regression scripts that stress-test recent implementations:
- **[scripts/test-kooko-pizza.ts](file:///Users/soluwrx/Downloads/PressPilot-OS/PressPilot-OS/scripts/test-kooko-pizza.ts)**: Validates restaurant-specific logic.
- **[scripts/generate-test-restaurants.ts](file:///Users/soluwrx/Downloads/PressPilot-OS/PressPilot-OS/scripts/generate-test-restaurants.ts)**: Generates multiple variations to check for edge cases in color mapping and layout.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **To the New AI Agent**: Always run `npx tsc --noEmit` locally before proposing changes to ensure you haven't introduced regressions. The Husky hook will block your commit if you do.
